{"id":666,"date":"2020-10-21T19:06:17","date_gmt":"2020-10-21T17:06:17","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/xanasoft.com\/?page_id=666"},"modified":"2023-04-29T07:41:23","modified_gmt":"2023-04-29T07:41:23","slug":"sbie2102","status":"publish","type":"page","link":"https:\/\/sandboxie-plus.com\/sandboxie\/sbie2102\/","title":{"rendered":"SBIE2102"},"content":{"rendered":"<h1>SBIE2102<\/h1>\n<p><strong>Message:<\/strong> SBIE2102 File is too large to copy into sandbox - <em>path<\/em><\/p>\n<p><strong>Logged To:<\/strong> <a href=\"PopupMessageLog\">Popup Message Log<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p><strong>Explanation:<\/strong><\/p>\n<p>This is an informational message.<\/p>\n<p>Before a sandboxed program can make changes to a file that already exists in your computer, Sandboxie first must make a copy of this file in the sandbox.<\/p>\n<p>This works very well for small files (up to a few megabytes in size), as the copy operation completes very quickly. But for larger files, the copy operation may take a noticeable length of time.<\/p>\n<p>For example, suppose you created a backup for a DVD, in the form of a 4GB file. If a sandboxed program tries to access the file, Sandboxie would have to make a sandboxed copy of the 4 GB file. This would take several minutes to complete, and would cost 4 GB of disk space.<\/p>\n<p>For this reason, Sandboxie will only make copies of files that are below a certain size threshold. Files larger than this size will be considered read-only inside the sandbox, and any attempt to modify them will result in message SBIE2102.<\/p>\n<p>The size threshold and alert message can be configured in <a href=\"FileMigrationSettings\">Sandbox Settings &gt; File Migration<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p>Related <a href=\"SandboxieIni\">Sandboxie Ini<\/a> setting: <a href=\"CopyLimitKb\">CopyLimitKb<\/a>, <a href=\"CopyLimitSilent\">CopyLimitSilent<\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>SBIE2102 Message: SBIE2102 File is too large to copy into sandbox &#8211; path Logged To: Popup Message Log. Explanation: This is an informational message. Before a sandboxed program can make changes to a file that already exists in your computer, Sandboxie first must make a copy of this file in the sandbox. This works very &hellip; <a href=\"https:\/\/sandboxie-plus.com\/sandboxie\/sbie2102\/\" class=\"more-link\">Continue reading <span class=\"screen-reader-text\">SBIE2102<\/span> <span class=\"meta-nav\">&rarr;<\/span><\/a><\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":1,"featured_media":0,"parent":108,"menu_order":0,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","template":"","meta":{"footnotes":""},"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/sandboxie-plus.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/666"}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/sandboxie-plus.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/sandboxie-plus.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/page"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/sandboxie-plus.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/1"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/sandboxie-plus.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=666"}],"version-history":[{"count":2,"href":"https:\/\/sandboxie-plus.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/666\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":2220,"href":"https:\/\/sandboxie-plus.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/666\/revisions\/2220"}],"up":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/sandboxie-plus.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/pages\/108"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/sandboxie-plus.com\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=666"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}